(Then he just sort of slammed the window door.  AWFUL service. I will not be back.

One of the staff members who is often the only one there is particularly boorish. I've been turned away twice 20 minutes before closing because he's already thrown everything away, and claims it's because he has to close before the store actually closes. This would be more understandable if he wasn't so rude and dismissive. He will watch you impatiently (and stand a little too close) as you're browsing, even being the only patrons, and it's clear he thinks patrons are a waste of his time if they need a reasonable amount of time to decide if they want anything else. He also tends to throw orders together in a way that squishes the donuts and makes a mess. The back area is usually in disarray even on quiet days. Usually I can give benefit of the doubt once or twice but this happens EVERY TIME I'm there, including last night (April 6th) around 8pm, and I've heard similar experiences from friends who have also gone in during the evening shift.  Outside of this staff member, the closing time for this location needs to be changed online -- here it says they're open until 12am but the store closes at 10pm.
